  "body": "From my understanding componentDidUpdate is called after a component is re-rendered. However, if  I take the code from Facebook React tutorial and add these 2 functions to class Game (its codepen is here https://codepen.io/anon/pen/zNgBQV)\r\n```\r\nsleep(milliseconds) {\r\n    let start = new Date().getTime();\r\n    for (let i = 0; i < 1e7; i++) {\r\n      if ((new Date().getTime() - start) > milliseconds){\r\n        break;\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n  \r\n  componentDidUpdate() {\r\n    this.sleep(2500);\r\n  }\r\n```\r\nthen it takes 2.5 seconds after every click for react to update the page, instead of updating the DOM then sleep for 2 seconds. Is this an expected behavior? If I need a function that only triggers after the page is updated then what should I use?",
